headline: OpenAI unveils 'o3' reasoning AI models in test phase
summary: CEO Sam Altman said the AI startup plans to launch o3 mini by the end of January, and full o3 after that, as more robust large language models could outperform existing models and attract new investments and users.  OpenAI's new o3 and o3 mini models, which are in internal safety testing currently, will be more powerful than its previously launched o1 models, the company said.  Rival Alphabet's Google released the second generation of its AI model Gemini earlier in December, as the search giant aims to reclaim the lead in the AI technology race.

headline: Alphabet stock gains as AI innovations boost investor confidence
summary: Investing.com -- Alphabet Inc Class A (NASDAQ:GOOGL)'s shares have surged recently, outperforming the S&P 500 and Meta Platforms (NASDAQ:META), as new AI developments fuel investor optimism, BofA Securities said. Shares of Google parent have surged nearly 9% since Dec. 9. The brokerage cited recent launches like Google’s AI video generator Veo 2, Gemini 2.0, and the Willow quantum computing chip as key drivers of optimism, reaffirming the company’s leadership in AI technology.

headline: Why IonQ Rallied This Week
summary: Shares of IonQ, Inc. (NYSE: IONQ) rallied 11.6% this week through Thursday trading, according to data from S&P Global Market Intelligence.  On Monday, Morgan Stanley Joseph Moore upped his price target on IonQ from $14.90 to $37, saying, "We can't identify a clear catalyst for this kind of equity appreciation in the space over that time, but we do see continued indications that investment in quantum should continue growing at a rapid pace."
